data.title: Cate Blanchett: Movies, Photos, Videos, News, Biography & Birthday
data.meta_description: Cate Blanchett: Check out the list of all Cate Blanchett movies along with photos, videos, biography and birthday. Also find latest Cate Blanchett news on Times of India.
data.text:
Cate Blanchett to receive Share Her Journey Groundbreaker award at TIFF 2024

PTI / Jul 03, 2024, 12:52 (IST)

Cate Blanchett will be honoured with the TIFF Share Her Journey Groundbreaker Award at Fairmont Royal York Hotel. The award recognizes her contributions to the film industry and commitment to promoting diversity. Joining previous recipients like Patricia Arquette and Michelle Yeoh, Blanchett's achievements will be celebrated at the Toronto International Film Festival in September.

Rege-Jean Page teams up with Steven Soderbergh for spy thriller 'Black Bag'

PTI / Mar 06, 2024, 17:35 (IST)

Rege-Jean Page joins Steven Soderbergh's spy thriller film 'Black Bag' alongside Cate Blanchett and Michael Fassbender. The film reunites Soderbergh and Blanchett, who previously collaborated on 'The Good German' and 'Oceans 8', respectively. David Koepp writes the film. Casey Silver and Greg Jacobs produce the film. Page is set to star in 'The Saint' reboot.

Kate Winslet: To be mistaken for Cate Blanchett is a huge compliment

IANS / Feb 29, 2024, 12:44 (IST)

Kate Winslet talks about her experience of being mistaken for Cate Blanchett, appreciating it as a compliment. She shares the mix-up on the Graham Norton Show and at the American Museum of Natural History.

Ranveer Singh and Deepika Padukone give off power-couple vibes as they walk hand-in-hand at airport: Pics

etimes.in / Feb 13, 2024, 08:26 (IST)

Bollywood power couple Ranveer Singh and Deepika Padukone arrived at the Mumbai airport in style from a quick trip out of the city. They were seen rocking thick woolens as they walked out of the airport, hand-in-hand. Deepika will soon present at the BAFTA awards alongside David Beckham and Cate Blanchett.

Deepika Padukone to join David Beckham, Cate Blanchett as presenter at BAFTA Awards 2024

etimes.in / Feb 13, 2024, 07:17 (IST)

Bollywood star Deepika Padukone will turn presenter at the upcoming BAFTA awards. She will join a starry lineup of celebrities, including David Beckham, Cate Blanchett, Adjoa Andoh, Hugh Grant, Lily Collins, among many others to hand out awards at the upcoming show that will be held on February 18.

Epstein List: Ricky Gervais' Golden Globes 2020 monologue calling out Hollywood for ties to Jeffrey Epstein goes VIRAL

etimes.in / Jan 06, 2024, 14:40 (IST)

Controversy surrounds the Hollywood film industry as sealed court documents revealing a list of names associated with Jeffrey Epstein are released. Ricky Gervais' scathing monologue at the 2020 Golden Globes, in which he called out Hollywood's ties with Epstein, goes viral. Gervais mentions Ronan Farrow, an investigative reporter who exposed sexual abuse allegations against Harvey Weinstein and Epstein's financial ties with MIT. Gervais also takes a dig at Prince Andrew and Leonardo DiCaprio. The released court documents name over 170 people, including political figures, associated with Epstein.

Jeffery Epstine List: Leonardo DiCaprio, Cate Blanchett, Michael Jackson among celebrities named in unsealed documents - Here's Why

etimes.in / Jan 04, 2024, 11:38 (IST)

The recently released unsealed court documents in the civil lawsuit against Ghislaine Maxwell reveal the extensive network of people associated with Jeffrey Epstein. The list includes high-profile celebrities like Leonardo DiCaprio, Cate Blanchett, Michael Jackson, Naomi Campbell, Bruce Willis, Cameron Diaz, Kevin Spacey, and George Lucas. However, it is important to note that the inclusion of these names does not imply any wrongdoing on their part.

Andrew Garfield, Joaquin Phoenix, Cate Blanchette, Oscar Isaac appeal for ceasefire between Israel-Hamas

IANS / Oct 21, 2023, 17:30 (IST)

Hollywood celebrities including Andrew Garfield, Joaquin Phoenix, and Cate Blanchett have signed a letter to US President Joe Biden, appealing for an immediate ceasefire between Israel and Hamas. The letter condemns the killing of Palestinian and Israeli civilians and calls for de-escalation to prevent further loss of life. The conflict, which began when Hamas launched missiles from Gaza, has resulted in thousands of deaths, including foreign citizens and the destruction of the Gaza strip. The Israeli government has defended its actions, claiming that the targeted buildings were being used by Hamas as weapons depots.

A star-studded night at Louis Vuitton's Womenswear SS24 show

TIMESOFINDIA.COM / Oct 04, 2023, 13:00 (IST)

The Louis Vuitton Womenswear Spring/Summer 2024 show at Paris Fashion Week featured a star-studded front row, including Zendaya, Ana de Armas, Gemma Chan, Cate Blanchett, Jennifer Connelly, Pharrell Williams, Jaden Smith, and Felix from Stray Kids. The show showcased Nicolas Ghesqui√®re's blend of classic elegance and modern innovation, with breezy plaid silhouettes and corset tops. The event highlighted Louis Vuitton's enduring influence and commitment to pushing fashion boundaries.

Jennifer Aniston calls out cancel culture, wondering if there is any end to it

IANS / Aug 23, 2023, 14:12 (IST)

After getting caught up in the issue surrounding Jamie Foxx's reportedly anti-Semitic social media remark, actress Jennifer Aniston has now stepped out to call out cancel culture as an unpleasant trend, wondering whether it will ever cease. "I'm so over cancel culture," the 54-year-old actress declared, according to a portal.

Fans slam Aishwarya Rai Bachchan for failing to praise performances of Indian actresses: 'Not acknowledging her competition is classic Aishwarya'

etimes.in / Jul 10, 2023, 15:32 (IST)

A video of an old interview with Aishwarya Rai Bachchan is making rounds on the internet. In the interview, Aishwarya discussed actresses whose performances she enjoyed, including Meryl Streep and Cate Blanchett. However, some comments criticized her for not naming other beautiful women, and for not acknowledging her competition.

Martin Scorsese's 'Killers of the Flower Moon' starring Leonardo DiCaprio and Robert De Niro premieres at Cannes; film gets 9-minute standing ovation - WATCH

Reuters / May 21, 2023, 06:59 (IST)

The eagerly awaited film 'Killers of the Flower Moon', helmed by Martin Scorsese, received a nine-minute-long standing ovation at its world premiere at the 2023 Cannes Film Festival. The film stars legendary actors Leonardo DiCaprio, Robert DeNiro and Lily Gladstone in the lead roles.

Israel-Hamas conflict: 55 Hollywood stars Joaquin Phoenix, Cate Blanchett, Andrew Garfield, Dua Lipa call for ceasefire; say 'History is watching'

TNN & Agencies / Oct 21, 2023, 07:25 (IST)

A-list Hollywood celebrities including Cate Blanchett, Joaquin Phoenix, Ramy Youssef and Andrew Garfield penned a letter to US President Joe Biden on Friday, urging him to call for a ceasefire in Israel's war with Hamas. "We urge your administration, and all world leaders, to honor all of the lives in the Holy Land and call for and facilitate a ceasefire without delay -- an end to the bombing of Gaza, and the safe release of hostages," said the letter, released by artists4ceasefire.org.

Ram Charan can't wait to see Cate Blanchett and Tom Cruise at the Oscars 2023

etimes.in / Mar 08, 2023, 15:55 (IST)

This year, at the Oscars on March 12, 2023, Ram Charan will accompany SS Rajamouli and Jr NTR on the red carpet. The nomination of RRR's "Naatu Naatu" for Best Original Song has made history. Prior to the ceremony, the celebrities are currently in the USA. During an interview with an American TV channel, Ram Charan expressed his excitement about meeting Hollywood actors he had admired since his childhood.
